<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >Virtual Proctoring</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resTwoColTwoOne section">









  
















 
	


<div class="row">
	
		<div class="col-md-8">
			<div class="stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="0190760d-0082-474c-b3ab-7b04f6594d95" >

    <p>Ryerson strongly recommends that instructors redesign traditional high stakes assessments, like midterm and final exams, for remote teaching whenever possible (e.g. lower their weight in the grading scheme, convert them to open book or <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TLxW2GSMRNHNjoSf3U71Ondpx1PN1MiUMsAoUFlj_hs/edit?usp=sharing"><span class="sr-only">google doc</span>take home<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-word-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, use <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/content/dam/learning-teaching/teaching-resources/assessment/alternative-assessments.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>alternative assessments<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a>, etc.).&nbsp;</p> 
<p>If after careful consideration the circumstances still require a proctored examination, Ryerson has made available a virtual proctoring tool, <strong>Respondus LockDown Browser + Respondus Monitor</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>Proctortrack</strong>.&nbsp;However, virtual proctoring tools do not fully replace the integrity of invigilated in-person examinations.</p> 
<p>Zoom or any other web conferencing tool is strongly NOT recommended to be used for live proctoring of midterm or final examinations. There is no way to ensure student privacy with Zoom. In Zoom, students will have to enable their webcam for the proctoring, which means that in the identification verification process, students will see other students showing their Ryerson OneCard. Students will also see other students and their spaces while taking the exam. Furthermore, Ryerson’s Office of the General Counsel advises against recording Zoom-administered examinations.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#0190760d-0082-474c-b3ab-7b04f6594d95");});</script></div>

				</div>

		</div> 
		
		
		
			<div class="clearfix visible-sm-block"></div>
		
		
			<div class="clearfix visible-xs-block"></div>
		
	
		<div class="col-md-4">
			<div class="stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resInfographic section">

























<div class="infoContainer style2 hasIcon">
	<div class="contentWrapper">
		<div class='iconContainer'><img class='icon' src='/etc.clientlibs/ryecms/static/icons/resources/svg/svg-04.svg' alt='' role='img' aria-hidden='true'/></div>
		<div class="textContainer"><p>While virtual proctoring tools can act as a <span class="resInfographicBold">deterrent</span> to academic misconduct, the tools come with some <span class="resInfographicBold"><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/centre-for-excellence-in-learning-and-teaching/remote-teaching/virtual-proctoring/considerations/#drawbacks">drawbacks</a></span> that should be considered before adopting them.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>

</div>

				</div>

		</div> 
		
			<div class="clearfix visible-lg-block"></div>
		
		
