</div></div>

				

				
				<div class="resAccordion section">
























 


<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <div class="panel-group accordion background-opaque" id="39602171-5769-430e-ad41-86a1d4630ece" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
			
				<div class="resAccordionControl" role="group" aria-label="Accordion Actions">
					<button class="resAccordionOpenAll">Open All</button> <button class="resAccordionCloseAll">Close All</button>
				</div>
				<script type="text/javascript">$(document).ready(function(){ initResAccordionControl("39602171-5769-430e-ad41-86a1d4630ece", true); });</script>
			
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1603848452249-what-is-virtual-proctoring-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#39602171-5769-430e-ad41-86a1d4630ece" href="#accordion-content-1603848452249-what-is-virtual-proctoring-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1603848452249-what-is-virtual-proctoring-" aria-expanded="false">
                            What is virtual proctoring?
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1603848452249-what-is-virtual-proctoring-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1603848452249-what-is-virtual-proctoring-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1603848452249 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="c5c79b89-9d81-4640-921d-1dba0ce46543" >

    <p>Virtual proctoring platforms use a combination of software and a student’s webcam to monitor a student as they complete an assessment. These platforms can also involve browser lockdown software that prevents a student from opening additional applications and windows while they are taking an exam. Virtual proctoring software can be either automated or live. With automated proctoring, software algorithms monitor the student for suspicious behaviours and flag those for the professor to review. Live virtual proctoring involves a proctor observing the student through their webcam as they complete their exam. Ultimately, the goal of virtual proctoring is to ensure that the student who is taking the test or exam is who they claim to be, and are not engaging in academic misconduct (Eckenrode, Ricci, &amp; Klingen, 2016).</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#c5c79b89-9d81-4640-921d-1dba0ce46543");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="ceecaa15-b171-4fd2-9a31-2fb95c36e53f" >

    <h3>References</h3> 
